# CHANGELOG.md is managed by release-please (googleapis/release-please-action).
# release-please generates its release sections in its own markdown style,
# which prettier then reformats — every release PR failed the
# `pre-commit · all hooks` check on a prettier CHANGELOG reflow, and manual
# `[Unreleased]` edits hit the same reflow churn (caught 4+ times in CI
# across batches). The CHANGELOG is prose; prettier adds ~no value there.
# Ignoring it ends that whole class of failure and keeps release-please's
# output authoritative.
CHANGELOG.md

# Helm chart templates (slice 038) embed Go-template `{{ ... }}` directives
# that are NOT valid YAML — prettier would mangle the control flow and the
# `nindent` whitespace that Helm rendering depends on. The pure-YAML chart
# files (Chart.yaml, values.yaml, values-production.yaml) stay
# prettier-managed; only templates/ and NOTES.txt are ignored.
deploy/helm/templates/

# Golden snapshot files (slice 172 + future schema-stability tests) are
# generated by `go test ... -update` with canonical Go-stdlib JSON
# indentation. Prettier reflows the input-schema sub-objects to its
# own preferred form, which trips the schema-stability test (the
# regenerator's bytes vs prettier's bytes don't match). Keep prettier
# out of testdata/ entirely — these files are tool-generated; humans
# don't read them in editors.
**/testdata/*.golden.json

# Slice-status artifacts generated/appended by scripts/gen-status.sh and
# scripts/slice-event.sh. `_STATUS.md` is regenerated on every `just status`
# in the generator's own markdown style; `_events.jsonl` is append-only JSONL
# (one object per line — prettier would reflow it and break the format);
# `_STATUS_HISTORY.md` is a frozen archival log. Same generated-file rationale
# as CHANGELOG.md above: prettier adds no value and its reflow churns against
# the tool output.
docs/issues/_STATUS.md
docs/issues/_STATUS_HISTORY.md
docs/issues/_events.jsonl
